hjson-cpp
------------------------------------------
Hjson is a syntax extension to JSON. It's NOT a proposal to replace JSON or to
incorporate it into the JSON spec itself. It's intended to be used like a user
interface for humans, to read and edit before passing the JSON data to the
machine.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libhjson-devel-2.2-1bl2
  libhjson2-2.2-1bl2
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hjson/hjson-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hjson/hjson-cpp/archive/refs/tags/2.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack hjson-cpp-2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./hjson-cpp-2.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hjson-cpp-2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/hjson-cpp-2.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhjson2-2.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhjson-devel-2.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(hjson-cpp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/hjson-cpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/hjson-cpp/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/hjson-cpp/README.md

(libhjson2)
  /usr/bin/cyghjson-2.dll

(libhjson-devel)
  /usr/include/hjson.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/hjson/hjson-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/hjson/hjson-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/hjson/hjson-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/hjson/hjson.cmake
  /usr/lib/libhjson.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/hjson-cpp.pc

